<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=96842775413272></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f96842775413272><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=13&mid=96842775413272>RE: Crowd control strategies:</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=13&mid=96842775413272#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Sep 8th 11:42 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Short note, less experienced players or ignorant ones make crowd control difficult.&nbsp;&nbsp;If you cant tutor your group to fight 1 mob at a time quickly, just give up and use charm.  If you keep pestering them, they just think you are a jerk.  At least with charm you reduce crowd by 1 and add to group by 1... not a bad change in odds.  Just my opinion.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
